description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ascenti is the leading provider of physiotherapy and associated services in the UK – helping people to elevate their health and live active lives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an ambitious, driven and experienced physiotherapist with a special interest in musculoskeletal physiotherapy, to join our dynamic team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job summary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Locations:Wyre Forest&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Contract type: Permanent &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hours:Full-time 40 hours/ part-time negotiable &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Salary band: Band E (APP) - £40,000 - £50,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Suitable for graduate applications:Yes/No&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;What it takes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As an Advanced Physiotherapist Practitioner you will be a key member of the Ascenti team and responsiblefor delivering an outstanding service to our patients and partners on a day-to-day basis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will uphold our company values and high standards, whilst building strong relationships with internal and external stakeholders. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be responsible for acting independently in the management of an often complex and chronic NHS MSK caseload, and for the diagnosing and treatment planning for these patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This will involve referrals into imaging and analysis/interpretation of results and knowledge of all possible multidisciplinary treatment pathways, and appropriate referral to these. Examples include: physiotherapy, surgery, Functional Restoration Service and Chronic Pain Service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;To view the full role profile please download the attached PDF. Please note thatyour salary package will be determined once we have had the opportunity to review your skills and experience against our key skills framework at your interview.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Ascenti difference&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our physiotherapist roles come with an industry leading training package, a clear progression pathway, bonus potential and much more.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a flexible employer that will put you at the centre of everything we do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We believe in supporting you to become the best version of yourself. There are quick career progression opportunities with no ceiling, allowing you to reach your potential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Depending on the location, the contract type available in the region and availability, our physiotherapists will have the opportunity to manage varied caseloads across different service lines, such as the NHS, occupational health, medico-legal and private medical insurance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This will enable you to widen your skills and experience, whilst helping you to progress your career and develop expertise in the areas of MSK physio that you are the most passionate about. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will also have the potential to earn more money through our self-funded/private patient incentive bonus scheme, whereby we will provide you with support to help you build your own caseload and treat more privately paying patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;What we can offer you&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clear banding structure aiding promotion and professional growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum of 100 hours of protected CPD time annually.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to a unique eLearning platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity to apply for a promotion once a year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Split role opportunities where you can combine a Disability Analyst role alongside our physiotherapy roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities for flexible working hours if available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relocation support packages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;33 days of annual leave (including bank holidays).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Healthcare cash plan enabling you to claim money back on health expenses such as dental.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to hundreds of retail and gym discounts through Bupa rewards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discounted physio for you, friends and family.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pension scheme with a salary exchange agreement option.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employee telephone counselling support (accessible 24 hours a day, 7 days per week).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cycle to work scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Company-wide and regional social events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical banding structure and salaries&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Ascenti clinical banding structure clearly sets out how you can progress your career and salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our highly experienced team of clinical service leads will be with you every step of the way to help you reach your professional goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each banding level has a clear set of development goals and competencies that you will need to demonstrate to progress.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The below is designed as a rough salary guide, but where you are on the scale will depend on several factors including location and experience. This will be determined at the interview stage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working outside London&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band A - £22,500 - £27,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band B - £27,000 - £31,500&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band C - £31,500 - £36,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band D - £36,000- £40,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band E (APP)- £40,000- £50,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
